name: Coles Kitchen Honey Soy & Garlic Stir Fry Sauce | 200g
description:
Coles Kitchen Real Food Fast Honey, Soy and Garlic Stir Fry Sauce 200g.

Ready in minutes
No artificial colours and flavours
Delicious blend of sweet honey, savoury soy and garlic

Cook up a family favourite with Coles Kitchen Honey, Soy Garlic Stir Fry Sauce.
This classic combination of garlic, sweet honey and savoury soy packs a flavour punch and is great paired with chicken, beef or pork strips. For a tasty vegetarian option try swapping out the meat for firm fried tofu. You can use any vegetables you have on hand, but broccoli, cauliflower and snow peas are all popular choices.

Coles Kitchen Honey, Soy and Garlic Stir Fry Sauce helps you cut down on meal prep so dinner comes together fast. Just make sure you have all your ingredients ready to go before you fire up the stove because the actual cooking happens quickly. Part of what makes stir fries great is their versatility so feel free to get creative with Coles Kitchen Honey, Soy and Garlic Stir Fry Sauce and different veggies and toppings. Serve with Hokkien noodles or fluffy rice.

Coles Kitchen tip: Build even more flavour into your dish with a sprinkling of chopped spring onions and chilli flakes.

idx: Ind56SColes_ADairy, Eggs & Fridge_SAReady to eat meals_IGarlos Junior Sausage Rolls 12 pack | 780g
name: Garlos Junior Sausage Rolls 12 pack | 780g
description:
Garlo's Pies is an Australian owned and operated family business which opened its first pie shop in Maroubra, Sydney 2001. The name Garlo comes from the nickname of father and sons, Terry, Sean and Nathan Garlick. Terry a retired mechanic/wharfie, Sean an ex footballer with the Rabbitohs and Roosters and Nathan a master Pastry Chef and lifetime pie lover.
Heating Instructions
Convection Oven (Preferred)
Preheat oven 175C. Remove from wrapping but leave in foil tray and place on baking tray. If frozen heat for 35-45 mins. If refrigerated heat for 20-25mins
Microwave Oven (800 watt)
A microwave may be used to speed up heating time. Remove from wrapping and foil tray and wrap pie in paper towel. If frozen heat on high for 5 minutes. If refrigerated heat on high for 1 min 30 seconds. To make pastry crispy after microwaving, remove paper towel, return to foil tray and place on baking tray in convention oven for 4 minutes at 200C.

name: Garlos Chunky Steak Pie | 200g
description:
Garlo's Pies is an Australian owned and operated family business which opened its first pie shop in Maroubra, Sydney 2001. The name Garlo comes from the nickname of father and sons, Terry, Sean and Nathan Garlick. Terry a retired mechanic/wharfie, Sean an ex footballer with the Rabbitohs and Roosters and Nathan a master Pastry Chef and lifetime pie lover.
Heating Instructions
Convection Oven (Preferred)
Preheat oven 175C. Remove from wrapping but leave in foil tray and place on baking tray. If frozen heat for 35-45 mins. If refrigerated heat for 20-25mins
Microwave Oven (800 watt)
A microwave may be used to speed up heating time. Remove from wrapping and foil tray and wrap pie in paper towel. If frozen heat on high for 5 minutes. If refrigerated heat on high for 1 min 30 seconds. To make pastry crispy after microwaving, remove paper towel, return to foil tray and place on baking tray in convention oven for 4 minutes at 200C.

name: Garlos Spinach & Feta Roll | 180g
description:
Garlo's Pies is an Australian owned and operated family business which opened its first pie shop in Maroubra, Sydney 2001. The name Garlo comes from the nickname of father and sons, Terry, Sean and Nathan Garlick. Terry a retired mechanic/wharfie, Sean an ex footballer with the Rabbitohs and Roosters and Nathan a master Pastry Chef and lifetime pie lover.
Heating Instructions
Convection Oven (Preferred)
Preheat oven 175C. Remove from wrapping but leave in foil tray and place on baking tray. If frozen heat for 35-45 mins. If refrigerated heat for 20-25mins
Microwave Oven (800 watt)
A microwave may be used to speed up heating time. Remove from wrapping and foil tray and wrap pie in paper towel. If frozen heat on high for 5 minutes. If refrigerated heat on high for 1 min 30 seconds. To make pastry crispy after microwaving, remove paper towel, return to foil tray and place on baking tray in convention oven for 4 minutes at 200C.

Coles Kitchen Sweet and Sour Stir Fry Sauce 200g.

Vegetarian
Traditional sweet and sour sauce
No artificial colours and flavours

Coles Sweet Sour Stir Fry Sauce is a quick and a convenient way to get delicious mid-week meals on the table with no fuss.

This tangy blend of spices is perfectly balanced with sweet pineapple and aromatic herbs providing a refreshing contrast to a variety of ingredients. For protein, chicken or pork strips are classic choices, especially when paired with pineapple chunks and crunchy vegetables like broccoli and carrots. For a tasty meat-free option, try Coles Sweet and Sour Stir Fry Sauce with fried tofu and vegetables to add colour and texture to the dish. Feel free to get creative and customise your stir-fries with whatever ingredients you have on hand.

Serve over noodles or rice and garnish with fresh spring onion and a sprinkling of sesame seeds for a vibrant family-friendly meal that's sure to be a hit.

Chefs Tip: For a spicy twist, add some sliced red chilli or chilli flakes.

idx: Ind56SColes_ADairy, Eggs & Fridge_SAReady to eat meals_IGarlos Lean Beef Pie | 200g
name: Garlos Lean Beef Pie | 200g
description:
Garlo's Pies is an Australian owned and operated family business which opened its first pie shop in Maroubra, Sydney 2001. The name Garlo comes from the nickname of father and sons, Terry, Sean and Nathan Garlick. Terry a retired mechanic/wharfie, Sean an ex footballer with the Rabbitohs and Roosters and Nathan a master Pastry Chef and lifetime pie lover.
Heating Instructions
Convection Oven (Preferred)
Preheat oven 175C. Remove from wrapping but leave in foil tray and place on baking tray. If frozen heat for 35-45 mins. If refrigerated heat for 20-25mins
Microwave Oven (800 watt)
A microwave may be used to speed up heating time. Remove from wrapping and foil tray and wrap pie in paper towel. If frozen heat on high for 5 minutes. If refrigerated heat on high for 1 min 30 seconds. To make pastry crispy after microwaving, remove paper towel, return to foil tray and place on baking tray in convention oven for 4 minutes at 200C.

idx: Ind56SColes_ADairy, Eggs & Fridge_SAReady to eat meals_IColes Kitchen Sweet & Sour Stir Fry Sauce | 200g
name: Coles Kitchen Sweet & Sour Stir Fry Sauce | 200g
description:
Coles Kitchen Sweet and Sour Stir Fry Sauce 200g.

Vegetarian
Traditional sweet and sour sauce
No artificial colours and flavours

Coles Sweet Sour Stir Fry Sauce is a quick and a convenient way to get delicious mid-week meals on the table with no fuss.

This tangy blend of spices is perfectly balanced with sweet pineapple and aromatic herbs providing a refreshing contrast to a variety of ingredients. For protein, chicken or pork strips are classic choices, especially when paired with pineapple chunks and crunchy vegetables like broccoli and carrots. For a tasty meat-free option, try Coles Sweet and Sour Stir Fry Sauce with fried tofu and vegetables to add colour and texture to the dish. Feel free to get creative and customise your stir-fries with whatever ingredients you have on hand.

Serve over noodles or rice and garnish with fresh spring onion and a sprinkling of sesame seeds for a vibrant family-friendly meal that's sure to be a hit.

Chefs Tip: For a spicy twist, add some sliced red chilli or chilli flakes.

name: Coles Kitchen Honey Soy & Garlic Stir Fry Sauce | 200g
description:
Coles Kitchen Real Food Fast Honey, Soy and Garlic Stir Fry Sauce 200g.

Ready in minutes
No artificial colours and flavours
Delicious blend of sweet honey, savoury soy and garlic

Cook up a family favourite with Coles Kitchen Honey, Soy Garlic Stir Fry Sauce.
This classic combination of garlic, sweet honey and savoury soy packs a flavour punch and is great paired with chicken, beef or pork strips. For a tasty vegetarian option try swapping out the meat for firm fried tofu. You can use any vegetables you have on hand, but broccoli, cauliflower and snow peas are all popular choices.

Coles Kitchen Honey, Soy and Garlic Stir Fry Sauce helps you cut down on meal prep so dinner comes together fast. Just make sure you have all your ingredients ready to go before you fire up the stove because the actual cooking happens quickly. Part of what makes stir fries great is their versatility so feel free to get creative with Coles Kitchen Honey, Soy and Garlic Stir Fry Sauce and different veggies and toppings. Serve with Hokkien noodles or fluffy rice.

Coles Kitchen tip: Build even more flavour into your dish with a sprinkling of chopped spring onions and chilli flakes.

idx: Ind56SColes_ADairy, Eggs & Fridge_SA_IGarlos Chunky Steak Pie | 200g
name: Garlos Chunky Steak Pie | 200g
description:
Garlo's Pies is an Australian owned and operated family business which opened its first pie shop in Maroubra, Sydney 2001. The name Garlo comes from the nickname of father and sons, Terry, Sean and Nathan Garlick. Terry a retired mechanic/wharfie, Sean an ex footballer with the Rabbitohs and Roosters and Nathan a master Pastry Chef and lifetime pie lover.
Heating Instructions
Convection Oven (Preferred)
Preheat oven 175C. Remove from wrapping but leave in foil tray and place on baking tray. If frozen heat for 35-45 mins. If refrigerated heat for 20-25mins
Microwave Oven (800 watt)
A microwave may be used to speed up heating time. Remove from wrapping and foil tray and wrap pie in paper towel. If frozen heat on high for 5 minutes. If refrigerated heat on high for 1 min 30 seconds. To make pastry crispy after microwaving, remove paper towel, return to foil tray and place on baking tray in convention oven for 4 minutes at 200C.
item_ingredients: Filling (65%): Beef 51%, Water, Thickener 1422, Soy Protein, Seasoning (Salt, Sugar, Caramel Colour (e150c), Dehydrated Vegetables (Onion, Garlic), Flavour (635), Hydrolysed Vegetable Protein, Corn Flour, Rice Flour, Spices, Spice Extract), Spices Pastry (35%): Wheat Flour, Margarine (Vegetable Oil, Water, Salt, Emulsifier (471, 472c), Antioxidant (304), Natural Flavour)), Malted Wheat Flour, Whey Powder (Milk, Sugar, Acidity Regulator (262)), Pastry Conditioner, Glaze (Milk Solids, Acidity Regulators (500, 451), Dried Glucose Syrup, Colour (160b)) Beef is 32% of filling and pastry combined.
